    <h1>🍽️ About EatWhere</h1>
    <p>Welcome to <strong>EatWhere</strong> — our office lunch spot finder!</p>

    <p>After months (or even years!) of eating out near the office, we noticed a recurring problem:</p>

    <blockquote>
      “Where to eat ah?”<br />
      “Same old places again?”<br />
      “Oh, is the place halal certified?"<br />
      "Today Ken not joining, shall we have vegetarian?”
    </blockquote>

    <p>We get it. Lunch should be something to look forward to — not a midday headache.</p>

    <h2>🥢 What is EatWhere?</h2>
    <p><strong>EatWhere</strong> is a light, fun, and practical web app to help you discover 
      <strong>good food around MDDI</strong>, especially when you're out of ideas or have teammates with different dietary needs.</p>

    <h2>🍛 What You Can Do</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>🔍 Filter by cuisine, dietary options, price</li>
      <li>📍 Browse curated listings of nearby food spots</li>
      <li>🎲 Get “Go Lucky” suggestions for something random</li>
      <li>💬 Read and write (upcoming soon) reviews to help others</li>
      <li>➕ Submit new food places for the team</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>💬 Why We Built This</h2>
    <p>Because food matters and team bonding over meals matters.</p>
    <p>Whether you’re looking for something affordable, accommodating dietary needs, or just trying not to eat at the same old kopitiam again — EatWhere is here to help you <strong>eat better, together</strong>.</p>

    <h2>🚀 Built With ❤️</h2>
    <p>A Techup (run 4) prototype turned passion project — made by people who love food and building things that help others.</p>
